<item>
            <title>[LU-18198] lfsck-performance:test_5a to check availability of OST inodes</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18198</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;lfs-performance:test_5a creates up to UNIT * MDSCOUNT * MAXSUBDIR files striped over all OSTs.&lt;br/&gt;
For MDSCOUNT=4, UNIT=8192, MAXSUBDIR=4 it fails like:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;..
+++++ Start cycle mdscount=3 at: Tue Sep  3 14:26:40 MSK 2024 +++++
..
open(/mnt/lustre_lfsck_1_2/d5a.lfsck-performance/1/2/f7484) error: File too large
..
 lfsck-performance test_5a: @@@@@@ FAIL: (14) Fail to gen 8192 files under /mnt/lustre_lfsck_1_3/d5a.lfsck-performance/1/3
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The test should check that there are enough inodes on OSTs.&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
